WEBVTT

00:04:57.960 --> 00:05:01.743
CA: So a moral system is the rules
by which we should treat each other

00:05:01.767 --> 00:05:03.332
or not treat each other.

00:05:03.356 --> 00:05:06.386
How do you create the rules
by which to treat each other?

00:05:06.410 --> 00:05:10.218
I mean, how do you build
a moral system from the ground up?

00:05:10.242 --> 00:05:13.410
SH: Just imagine that we have
no notion of "should" or "ought."

00:05:13.434 --> 00:05:15.384
There's nothing we should do.

00:05:15.408 --> 00:05:17.767
This thought has not
occurred to anyone yet.

00:05:17.791 --> 00:05:20.458
And even the notion
of right and wrong and good and evil

00:05:20.482 --> 00:05:21.735
hasn't occurred to anyone.

00:05:21.759 --> 00:05:23.776
We just find ourselves in this universe,

00:05:23.800 --> 00:05:26.904
and this circumstance
which we didn't create

00:05:26.928 --> 00:05:30.693
is one in which conscious
minds like our own